<?xml version="1.0"?>
<Recipe>
  <Title image="Eggplant Parmesan_EggplantParmesan.jpg" name="Eggplant Parmesan" category="SIDE" cuisine="ITALIAN">
    <Yield amount="8" units="SERVING"/>
    <Times prep="" cook=""/>
  </Title>
  <Nutrition calories="" fat="" carbs="" protein="" sugar="" sodium="" fiber="" servings="1" servingsUnit="CUP"/>
  <Description>When summer gardens are producing heavily, the neighbors, regretting having planted four hills of eggplants/zucchini, will begin conducting night raids in their block, hiding them under newspaper deliveries and in mailboxes, etc. -anything to get rid of them. Here's one way.</Description>
  <Prerequisites>
    <Prerequisite>Make &lt;a href='/GetRecipe?recipeName=Marinara'&gt;Marinara Sauce&lt;/a&gt;, to get rid of some of those tomatoes.</Prerequisite>
    <Prerequisite>Cut eggplant into 1/2 inch slices.  A lot of people recommend salting the slices and stacking them in a colander under weight until some of the juice leaches out, supposedly to draw out any bitterness, and make them easier to fry. </Prerequisite>
    <Prerequisite>Setup for treating &lt;a href='/GetRecipe?recipeName=Standard%20Breading%20Method%20-%20A%20l%27Alglaise'&gt; l'Alglaise&lt;/a&gt;.</Prerequisite>
    <Prerequisite>Preheat oven to 400°F.</Prerequisite>
  </Prerequisites>
  <Ingredients>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Eggplant</Name>
      <Quantity units="EACH">2</Quantity>
      <Prep>SLICED</Prep>
      <Notes>See Prerequisites.</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>&lt;a href='/GetRecipe?recipeName=Marinara%20Sauce'&gt;Marinara Sauce&lt;/a&gt;</Name>
      <Quantity units="CUP">2</Quantity>
      <Prep>NONE</Prep>
      <Notes/>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Mozzarella Cheese</Name>
      <Quantity units="CUP">1</Quantity>
      <Prep>SHREAD</Prep>
      <Notes/>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>&lt;a href='/GetRecipe?recipeName=Parmesanr'&gt;Parmesan CHeese&lt;/a&gt;</Name>
      <Quantity units="CUP">.5</Quantity>
      <Prep>GRATE</Prep>
      <Notes/>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Light Oil</Name>
      <Quantity units="CUP">.5</Quantity>
      <Prep>NONE</Prep>
      <Notes>For pan frying.</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>AP Flour</Name>
      <Quantity units="CUP">1</Quantity>
      <Prep>NONE</Prep>
      <Notes>For breading, as needed.</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Eggs</Name>
      <Quantity units="EACH">2</Quantity>
      <Prep>BEATEN</Prep>
      <Notes>For breading, as needed.</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Breac Crumbs</Name>
      <Quantity units="CUP">1</Quantity>
      <Prep>NONE</Prep>
      <Notes>For breading, as needed.</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Kosher/Sea Salt</Name>
      <Quantity units="TSP">1</Quantity>
      <Prep>NONE</Prep>
      <Notes>To taste.</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Black Pepper</Name>
      <Quantity units="TSP">.5</Quantity>
      <Prep>NONE</Prep>
      <Notes>To taste.</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Parsley</Name>
      <Quantity units="TBSP">1</Quantity>
      <Prep>CHOPFINE</Prep>
      <Notes/>
    </Ingredient>
    <Ingredient>
      <Name>Fresh Basil</Name>
      <Quantity units="SPRIG">3</Quantity>
      <Prep>NONE</Prep>
      <Notes>For garnish.</Notes>
    </Ingredient>
  </Ingredients>
  <Method>
    <Step image="">Place about a 1/2 inch of oil in a heavy skillet and heat to about 350°F - 375°F.</Step>
    <Step image="">Treat &lt;a href='/GetRecipe?recipeName=Standard%20Breading%20Method%20-%20A%20l%27Alglaise'&gt; l'Alglaise&lt;/a&gt;: Bread the eggplant by dredging in flour, dipping in egg and then dredging in bread crumbs. </Step>
    <Step image="">Fry, turning once, until GBD (golden-brown and delicious), season with salt and pepper and drain on paper towels.</Step>
    <Step image="">Put a layer of marinara sauce in an oven safe dish.  Add the fried eggplant slices and cover with more marinara sauce.  Top with mozzarella cheese.</Step>
    <Step image="">Cover and bake for 15 minutes.  Remove and bake for 5 more minutes or so until cheese begins to brown (or run under broiler).</Step>
    <Step image="">Garnish with basil, parsley and serve with parmesan cheese. </Step>
  </Method>
  <Variations/>
</Recipe>